.so fork.tmac
.SS TEXT STYLING
.PP
This set of functions affect how subsequent characters look.
.PP
.cdef_voidfunc set_bold_mode
.cdef_voidfunc set_italic_mode
.cdef_voidfunc set_reverse_mode
.cdef_voidfunc set_normal_mode
.sp -1
.IP
The
.BR bold ", " italic ", and " reverse
modes do not have a corresponding command for undoing
the style.
They are all reversed together with the
.B set_normal_mode
function.
.PP
.cdef_voidfunc start_standout_mode
.cdef_voidfunc stop_standout_mode
.sp -1
.IP
Standout mode is grouped separately from the other style modes
because it is not invocable by
.B groff-generated
documents, but may be used by
.B less
or other programs to distinguish instructions or other meta
information.


